I know of one person who showed up to Bucconeer Labor Day weekend,
only to discover it had been held weeks earlier.  At least people are
less likely to make that mistake these days, now that Worldcons move
around.

Speaking of moving around, curiously enough August 6-10 are also the
dates of the 2008 Worldcon.  Only once before have two consecutive
Worldcons been on the exact same dates (1946 - 1947).  The dates are
usually different if only because consecutive years never have the
same days of the week fall on the same dates.  Next year's Worldcon
will be held Wednesday through Sunday, 2009's Thursday through Monday.

I updated the appropriate Wikipiedia pages with the 2009 info.  In
doing so I noticed that the only Tom Doherty listed in Wikipedia is a
hockey player.  And not even a professional hockey player.  He's just
14.  I thought that odd, especially since all the links that point to
Tom Doherty's page are obviously intended to point to the publisher.
I see that that page *was* about the publisher until a few months ago,
at which point someone completely replaced it with badly written text
about a totally non-noteworthy teenager.  So I reverted it.  I see
that this had happened, and been reverted, once before.  I'll keep an
eye out for further vandalism to that page.
